					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-7136807#post-3924956</guid>
				<title>(no title)</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-7136807/scp-4949#post-3924956</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Sat, 25 Aug 2018 01:44:46 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>Uncle Nicolini</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>3487700</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>We originally wanted it to make the parents get sick with a random ailment (ranging from a cold to stage 4 cancer) which would then allow the child to 'cure' their parent while enjoying some good old fashioned family fun.</p> <p>Dr. Wondertainment and dado are very big on family.</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-7136807#post-3924950</guid>
				<title>(no title)</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-7136807/scp-4949#post-3924950</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Sat, 25 Aug 2018 01:36:49 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>TL333s</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>1304786</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>Got to the end and tried to upvote again.</p> <p>This is a <em>good</em> dado skip. I love the suggested interactions between him and Wondertainment. I love how this actually works, what it lets the kids do. And I was <em>not ready</em> for the Supervising doctor's actions near the end. Quite the gut punch.</p> <p>It's possible I read this and just forgot already, but &#8212; at the risk of running into the hare removal pills &#8212; is there any effect if a non-child tries to use this kit? Or is it just so much plastic in an adult's hands?</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
